All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Symbol, TextSymbol
public class RasterShieldSymbol
extends BaseTextSymbol

This symbol is used for drawing highway shields with a specified background image.

The symbol supports the following attributes:

  • Antialiasing - antialiasing smooths out the "roughness" of an image by padding pixels with intermediate colors. This attribute can be true or false, and the default is false.

  • Transparency - this is a double value that can range from 0.0 to 1.0, and default is 1.0, which means no transparency

  • Font - the Font object used for the text string. The default is "Dialog", PLAIN, with a height of 12.

  • Color - the Color object used for the text. The default is black.

  • Shadow - The Color objects used for the shadow behind the shield. The default is null (no shadow).

  • FeatureWeight, LabelWeight, LabelBufferRatio, HowManyLabels, and LabelPriorities.

  • RotationalAngles, LineLabelPosition - these have a special meaning, see LabelEngine for details.

  • PrintMode defines the type of print mode: TitleCaps, AllUpper, AllLower or None, default is None.

  • LabelMode can be PrettyPrint, AllUpper, AllLower, Full, NumericOnly or None, default is None.

  • TextPositionX(Y) - these attributes control the aligment of the text string over the image, default is 0 pixel.

  • ImageString, UrlString - these take the full path or url to the image file. The imageString has first priority.

    • For example:

    RasterShieldSymbol ssSymbol = new RasterShieldSymbol;
    spSymbol.setImageString("c:/temp/shield.gif");
